EXISTED IN THE WIRED, DIDN'T I?
238
00:18:06,963 --> 00:18:10,066
- YES.
- YOU'RE EXACTLY THE SAME AS ME.
239
00:18:10,066 --> 00:18:12,268
YOU'RE OMNIPRESENT
IN THE WIRED
240
00:18:12,268 --> 00:18:14,003
FOREVER.
241
00:18:14,003 --> 00:18:16,138
WHEREVER ANYONE IS,
WHEREVER THEY GO,
242
00:18:16,138 --> 00:18:18,274
YOU HAVE ALWAYS
BEEN THERE.
243
00:18:18,274 --> 00:18:22,311
YOU'VE WATCHED WHAT THEY DIDN'T
ALLOW ANY OF THE OTHERS TO SEE.
244
00:18:22,311 --> 00:18:25,114
YOU'VE TOLD EVERYONE
ABOUT IT, THAT'S ALL.
245
00:18:25,114 --> 00:18:27,116
IT WAS THE RIGHT THING
TO DO.
246
00:18:27,116 --> 00:18:28,918
DON'T WORRY.
247
00:18:28,918 --> 00:18:32,455
THE WIRED'S INFORMATION
SHOULD BE SHARED, SHOULDN'T IT?
248
00:18:39,662 --> 00:18:43,299
- ALL OF IT--
ALL YOU'VE SAID--
249
00:18:43,299 --> 00:18:45,134
IT'S A LIE.
250
00:18:45,134 --> 00:18:47,503
- WHY IS THAT?
- ALICE AND ALL OF THE OTHERS--
251
00:18:47,503 --> 00:18:49,505
THEY SAID THAT THEY SAW ME
IN THE WIRED
252
00:18:49,505 --> 00:18:51,374
WHEN I KNOW
I WASN'T THERE.
253
00:18:51,374 --> 00:18:54,443
WHAT REALLY MATTERS IS THAT
AS LONG AS I'M AWARE OF MYSELF,
254
00:18:54,443 --> 00:18:58,915
MY TRUE SELF IS ALWAYS
RIGHT HERE INSIDE OF ME.
255
00:18:58,915 --> 00:19:00,917
YOU'RE TELLING ME
THAT YOU'VE BEEN PASSING OFF
256
00:19:00,917 --> 00:19:02,919
THESE DUPES AS ME
ALL ALONG?
257
00:19:02,919 --> 00:19:04,921
WHAT A LOAD
OF GARBAGE.
258
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:10,026
IF I'M REALLY--
259
00:19:10,026 --> 00:19:12,028
IF I'M REALLY
WHAT YOU SAY I AM,
260
00:19:12,028 --> 00:19:14,030
AND I'M TOTALLY DELUDED,
THEN--
261
00:19:14,030 --> 00:19:16,565
- THEN WHAT, LAIN?
262
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,336
- ALL THEIR MEMORIES
OF BEING SEEN BY LAIN--
263
00:19:20,336 --> 00:19:22,705
I COULD PERHAPS DELETE
THAT INFORMATION.
264
00:19:25,074 --> 00:19:27,076
- THAT'S TRUE.
265
00:19:27,076 --> 00:19:28,577
GIVE IT A TRY.
266
00:19:28,577 --> 00:19:31,580
YOU WERE BORN WITH THAT KIND
OF POWER INSIDE OF YOU.
267
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:54,370
- ( girls chattering,
laughing )
268
00:19:58,007 --> 00:20:00,409
- Girl: i'll be over
BY THE LOCKERS LATER.
269
00:20:00,409 --> 00:20:02,678
- Girl #2: no, of course not.
- Girl #1: see ya.
270
00:20:02,678 --> 00:20:04,146
- Alice: ¡LAIN!
271
00:20:06,682 --> 00:20:09,352
- ( giggling )
- HEY LAIN, WAIT UP.
272
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,356
- ( Lain's voice ) COULD THEY
REALLY HAVE FORGOTTEN?
273
00:20:13,356 --> 00:20:16,025
- ( laughing )
274
00:20:16,025 --> 00:20:18,427
- THEY FORGOT?
275
00:20:18,427 --> 00:20:21,230
- LAIN.
276
00:20:22,631 --> 00:20:25,034
- THEY REALLY DID.
277
00:20:25,034 --> 00:20:26,435
- ALICE.
278
00:20:30,406 --> 00:20:33,142
WH-- WHAT?
WHAT THE--?
279
00:20:33,142 --> 00:20:35,378
- ALICE.
280
00:20:35,378 --> 00:20:38,114
HEY, I WANT TO GO
TO CYBERIA TODAY.
281
00:20:38,114 --> 00:20:41,150
COME ON, LET'S GO.
- ( giggling )
282
00:20:41,150 --> 00:20:44,086
- I SECOND.
- THIS IS UNUSUAL.
283
00:20:44,086 --> 00:20:47,023
- SURE, WE CAN GET CHANGED
AT MY PLACE AGAIN
284
00:20:47,023 --> 00:20:49,025
AND GO FROM THERE.
- GREAT.
285
00:20:53,562 --> 00:20:56,098
HEY, ALICE, WHAT DO YOU THINK
I SHOULD WEAR?
286
00:20:56,098 --> 00:20:59,268
- STOP IT!
ALICE, I'M OVER HERE!  IT'S ME!
287
00:21:05,674 --> 00:21:08,377
I'M OVER HERE, ALICE.
288
00:21:08,377 --> 00:21:11,480
- Julie: come on, hurry up.
- Reika: hey, wait for me.
289
00:21:15,684 --> 00:21:17,787
- THAT'S RIGHT.
IT'S JUST LIKE YOU SAID--
290
00:21:17,787 --> 00:21:21,090
LAIN IS LAIN
AND I AM ME.
291
00:21:42,678 --> 00:21:44,680
- HELLO, NAVI.
292
00:21:45,714 --> 00:21:47,716
- HELLO, LAIN.
293
00:21:54,657 --> 00:21:56,659
- I AM ME.
294
00:21:56,659 --> 00:21:58,761
I'M THE ONLY ME, RIGHT?
295
00:21:58,761 --> 00:22:02,364
AND THERE ISN'T ANY OTHER ME
BUT ME.
296
00:22:02,364 --> 00:22:03,866
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?
297
00:22:15,811 --> 00:22:18,280
- ( theme song playing )
298
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:37,750
nan no tsumi mo nai hazu na no ni nanraka no batsu wo uketeru
299
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:37,750
Although I must be innocent, now I am punished
300
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:44,340
jibun de maita tane de mo nai no ni
301
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:44,340
I wasn't the one who sowed those seeds, but nevertheless
302
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:50,510
sakimidareta hana tsumasareru
303
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:50,510
I have to pull up the flowers that bloomed from them
304
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,690
shiranai koto to mo ienai ga
305
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,690
I can't say I didn't know about it
306
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:06,150
katabou katsuida oboe wa nai
307
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:06,150
but I don't remember taking any part in it
308
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:12,450
jiyuu wo takaku kawasareta ki mo suru ga
309
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:12,450
I think my freedom cost me dearly
310
00:23:12,870 --> 00:23:19,790
kokoro made yasuku utta oboe wa nai
311
00:23:12,870 --> 00:23:19,790
but I don't remember selling my soul so cheaply
312
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:27,800
hey hey kutabatte osaraba suru made
313
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:27,800
Hey hey, until I die and say farewell...
314
00:23:28,670 --> 00:23:37,560
hey hey dare no te ni mo kakaranai
315
00:23:28,670 --> 00:23:37,560
Ey ey... nadie puede tocarme
316
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:43,150
vagando por la noche lejana
317
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:43,150
Probablemente no sabes
318
00:23:43,150 --> 00:23:52,160
shiranai darou eien no narazu monotachi wo
319
00:23:43,150 --> 00:23:52,160
los bandidos eternos merodeando en la noche lejana